ut her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margred Eyton was born in Holt, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the daughter of Dafydd Eyton. She had at least 2 daughters."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1374–Female":"1374–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1374":"1374","1365":"1365","of,Holt,Denbighshire,Wales":"Holt, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1365–Female":"1365–Kuollut","1374–Female":"1374–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1374":"1374","1365":"1365","of,Holt,Denbighshire,Wales":"Holt, Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","1365–Female":"1365–Décédée","1374–Female":"1374–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1374":"1374","1365":"1365","of,Holt,Denbighshire,Wales":"Holt, Denbighshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margred Eyton est née à Holt, Denbighshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, fille de Dafydd Eyton. Elle a eu au moins 2 filles."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1365–Female":"1365–Verstorben","1374–Female":"1374–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1374":"1374","1365":"1365","of,Holt,Denbighshire,Wales":"Holt, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Margred Eyton wurde in Holt, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom, als Tochter von Dafydd Eyton geboren. Sie hatte mindestens 2 Töchter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","–Female":"Desede","1365–Female":"1365–Desede","